{
  "text": "As noted, MTP is a turning technique which produces discontinuous chips by superimposing oscillations in the tool feed direction to repeatedly interrupt the cutting process [CITATION_1] . An exaggerated depiction of an MTP turning operation is displayed in Fig. 2 . The broken chip length is dependent on two, user-defined MTP parameters: 1) the tool oscillation frequency relative to the spindle speed, OPR; and 2) the oscillation amplitude relative to the global feed per revolution, RAF. The parameters are defined as:",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "109512752"
